dsa.datastructures.stack

Class StackLinkedList

  • java.lang.Object
    • dsa.datastructures.linkedlist.Linked_List
      • dsa.datastructures.stack.StackLinkedList

  • public class StackLinkedList
extends Linked_List
    The StackLinkedList class contains stack operation which uses linked list to store data.

    StackLinkedList is thread-safe and is implemented for primitive types only.

    Time Complexity(Best) Time Complexity(Average) Time Complexity(Worst)
    Insert(puch) Ω(1) θ(n) O(n)
    Delete(pop) Ω(1) θ(n) O(n)
    See Also:
    Linked_List

      • pop

        public java.lang.Object pop()
        Removes the most recently added element.

        This method is equivalent to Linked_List.removeAtIndex(long) where index is size() - 1.

        Returns:
        the element at the top of the stack
        Throws:
        java.util.NoSuchElementException - if this stack is empty

      • peek

        public java.lang.Object peek()
        Retrieves, but does not remove, the top of stack.
        Returns:
        the top of stack, or null if the stack is empty
